      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 104: The macOS block accidentally appends `LOCAL_HOSTVARS\u003d...` to `VPX_CONF` and leaves the next `--extra-cxxflags` line as a top-level tab-indented line, which will either break make parsing or pass an invalid configure argument. It also overwrites `LOCAL_HOSTVARS` later without preserving `$(HOSTVARS)`, so the configure invocation can lose the intended compiler/toolchain environment. Keep the host vars assignment separate from `VPX_CONF` and append only configure flags to `VPX_CONF`.\n```suggestion\nifdef HAVE_MACOSX\nVPX_CONF +\u003d --extra-cxxflags\u003d\"$(EXTRA_COMMON) $(EXTRA_CXXFLAGS)\"\nLOCAL_HOSTVARS\u003d$(HOSTVARS) MACOSX_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET\u003d$(MIN_OSX_VERSION)\nendif\n```",
